1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,130
NewsLab turns a research plan into a controlled, browser-based news-feed study.

2
00:00:04,130 --> 00:00:08,535
Researchers configure assignment, sample targets, consent, completion, and

3
00:00:08,535 --> 00:00:12,390
condition-specific feed controls in one experiment workspace.

4
00:00:12,390 --> 00:00:15,313
Articles become approved content sets, with direct control

5
00:00:15,313 --> 00:00:17,870
over the sequence delivered to each condition.

6
00:00:17,870 --> 00:00:20,688
Optional AI providers can propose article variants.

7
00:00:20,688 --> 00:00:24,310
Every result enters a side-by-side human review before approval.

8
00:00:24,310 --> 00:00:27,510
Participants enter through study-specific consent, then continue into

9
00:00:27,510 --> 00:00:29,910
the experience assigned to their condition.

10
00:00:29,910 --> 00:00:33,162
The responsive feed supports scrolling, article views, and

11
00:00:33,162 --> 00:00:36,820
like, share, or save controls while recording each interaction.

12
00:00:36,820 --> 00:00:40,787
The configured survey follows naturally, supporting Likert, choice,

13
00:00:40,787 --> 00:00:42,770
and optional free-text questions.

14
00:00:42,770 --> 00:00:45,865
Back in the researcher workspace, participant and session

15
00:00:45,865 --> 00:00:48,960
summaries show progress while keeping preview records separate.

16
00:00:48,960 --> 00:00:52,746
Finally, NewsLab exports events, participants, exposures, and survey

17
00:00:52,746 --> 00:00:56,531
responses as structured CSV files with a data

18
00:00:56,531 --> 00:00:58,897
dictionary. Researchers define the questions;

19
00:00:58,897 --> 00:01:00,790
NewsLab runs the workflow.
